// Collab Manager
// Creates and manages collab sessions stored in .collab/sessions/ under a project directory.

Sessions are stored at .collab/sessions/<name>/. The old location .collab/<name>/ is
supported for backwards compatibility and is checked as a fallback in all read operations.
Session names follow an adjective-adjective-noun pattern and are guaranteed unique.

FUNCTION randomChoice(arr) -> T
  Return a random element from the array.

---

FUNCTION generateSessionName() -> string
  Pick two random adjectives and one random noun and join them with hyphens.

---

FUNCTION directoryExists(path) -> boolean
  Return true if the path exists and is a directory, false otherwise.

---

FUNCTION getCollabDir(baseDir) -> string
  Return the path to baseDir/.collab.

---

FUNCTION getSessionsDir(baseDir) -> string
  Return the path to baseDir/.collab/sessions.

---

FUNCTION hasOldSessionStructure(baseDir) -> boolean
  Scan .collab/ for subdirectories (excluding "sessions" and "kodex") that contain a
  collab-state.json file. Return true if any are found (indicating a pre-migration project).

---

FUNCTION listCollabSessions(baseDir) -> CollabSession[]                            EXPORT
  CALLS: getDisplayName (state-machine)
  Read sessions from the new location (.collab/sessions/) first, then the old location
  (.collab/) for backwards compatibility. For each session directory, parse collab-state.json
  and optionally metadata.json for the template. Skip duplicates already found in the new
  location. Sort sessions by lastActivity descending and return.

---

FUNCTION createCollabSession(baseDir, template, customName) -> { name, path }      EXPORT
  Create .collab/sessions/ if it doesn't exist.
  Use the provided name or generate one. Retry up to 10 times to find a unique name
  (checking both old and new locations). Throw if no unique name can be found.
  Create the session directory with diagrams/ and documents/ subdirectories.
  Write metadata.json and collab-state.json (state: "collab-start").
  Return the session name and path.

---

FUNCTION findSessionPath(baseDir, sessionName) -> string | null
  Check new location (.collab/sessions/<name>) first. If not found, check old location
  (.collab/<name>). Return the found path or null.

---

FUNCTION getCollabSessionState(baseDir, sessionName) -> CollabState               EXPORT
  Resolve the session path, then read and parse collab-state.json.
  Throw if session not found or file is invalid.

---

FUNCTION updateCollabSessionState(baseDir, sessionName, updates) -> CollabState   EXPORT
  Resolve the session path, read the current state, merge in the updates
  (always overwriting lastActivity with the current time), then write back.
  Return the merged state.

---

FUNCTION getCollabSessionPath(baseDir, sessionName) -> string                     EXPORT
  Resolve the actual path (new or old location). If found, return it.
  Otherwise return the default new-location path for session creation.

---

FUNCTION getCollabSessionPathSync(baseDir, sessionName) -> string                 EXPORT
  Return the new-location path synchronously without checking existence.
